reviews.review_text:
This one is the best yet for this fine show I was at this one, and was impressed at the show, even within the huge echoing chamber that was the Seattle Coliseum. However, the coliseum seemed to leave most recordings either overwhelmed by crowd noise or defeated by the venue. Finally, this one comes through! The crowd noise can be heard here and there and at appropriate moments, but while the music is playing there is amazingly clear sound throughout! Just listen to the clarity in the opening minutes of Sugaree! I've dreamed of having a really good recording of this show since 1979, and now at last, I can sit back and listen, completely satisfied. Surely the sound had never been this clear in the Seattle Coliseum? I can hardly believe it.

Listen to this one, it elevates this concert to a higher level than I remember.
Phenomenal Performance This one is a true gem. Excellent soundscape of a superb performance!
